English Premiership side Tottenham  Hotspur offered 2.3 million pounds (3.5 million dollars) for Olympique  Marseille's French international defender Basile Boli, according to the French  club on Satukrday.
It also revealed that Boli, who is being courted by Italian club Lazio,  was also interesting Arsenal.
Boli headed Marseille's winning goal in their 1-0 European Cup final win  over AC Milan at Munich last year.
He is set to join a series of big names who are leaving Marseille after  they were relegated to the French second division following a match-rigging  scandal.
